H.B. 1051
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 27, 2026
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH10595-MCa-318
Short Title: Funding for Senior Care/Community Health. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative K. Brown.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FUNDING TO IMPROVE HEALTHCARE AND STRENGTHEN
3 HEALTH SYSTEMS FOR SENIORS AND VULNERABLE POPULATIONS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
6 Budget and Management the sum of two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000) in
7 nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to MedAid
8 Foundation Incorporated, a nonprofit organization, to expand healthcare access, improve senior
9 care, and strengthen community health systems for vulnerable populations who face barriers to
10 healthcare access, including the lack of affordable supplies, limited preventive care, and
11 inadequate support from existing facilities.
12 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
*DRH10595-MCa-318*

